-- Gold Climbs to Record as Dollar Weakens After Federal Reserve's Statement
-- B y   W e n d y   P u g h
-- 2010-09-22T04:14:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-22/gold-climbs-to-record-as-dollar-weakens-after-federal-reserve-s-statement.html
Gold for immediate delivery
increased as much as 0.3 percent to a record $1,291.05 an ounce
after the Federal Reserve said it was willing to ease monetary
policy further to boost the U.S. economy. Gold futures gained to
an all-time high of $1,292.50 an ounce.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
